(20, 'Footer', 'Policies', 'payments-terms', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>GENERAL PAYMENTS TERMS</strong></p>\r\n<p>This section of the Payments Terms of Use applies to all Payment Services provided by Unipuller Payment Entities, collectively referred to as \"we\" or \"us\" in this section.</p>\r\n<p><strong>1. Overview of Payments on Unipuller Services</strong></p>\r\n<p>When you use Unipuller Services, you agree to Unipuller Payment Entities handling payments on your behalf, overseeing the settlement of payments to you, referred to as \"Managed Payments\" or \"Payment Services.\"</p>\r\n<p>Buyers can choose from various payment methods, including specific credit or debit cards, PayPal, Google Pay, Apple Pay, direct debit, \"Pay Later\" methods, Unipuller coupons, gift cards, or funds in a stored value account under Unipuller&rsquo;s Balance Terms and Conditions (currently available to selected U.S. sellers). We reserve the right to modify available payment methods at our discretion.</p>\r\n<p>The contractual agreement for a buyer\'s purchase directly occurs between you and the buyer. After a Managed Payments transaction, you\'ll receive a notification, and settlement to your Linked Financial Account (defined in Part I, Section 4 \"Seller Onboarding\") will be initiated by us. You can track transaction status in the Payments tab in the Seller Hub. In case of payment errors or erroneous fund receipt, we retain the right to recover such amounts from you.</p>\r\n<p><strong>2. Global Sales</strong></p>\r\n<p>Unipuller Payment Entities offer Payment Services, and you can avail these services from multiple Unipuller Payment Entities. Each entity is designated to handle transactions and oversee settlement for sales on specific sites. The Responsible Payment Entity is determined by the site where you list your item. Your \"Payout Entity\" is associated with your country of residence or business establishment. Disbursements to your Linked Financial Account are received from this entity, regardless of your item\'s listing location.</p>\r\n<p>If the Responsible Payment Entity aligns with your Payout Entity, your Payout Entity manages and settles the sale. If they differ, the Responsible Payment Entity handles the sale, transferring funds to your Payout Entity, which disburses them to your Linked Financial Account.</p>\r\n<p><strong>ECUK: Responsible Payment Entity for Sales on Unipuller.com, Payout Entity for UK, Jersey, Guernsey, Gibraltar Sellers</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Additional Payments Terms: VI. ADDITIONAL PAYMENTS TERMS FOR SERVICES PROVIDED BY Unipuller Commerce Ltd.</strong></p>\r\n<p>For sellers outside the EEA (except Iceland), the UK, and Switzerland, Payment Services by Unipuller.com and/or ECUK are temporarily suspended until an item listed on an EEA, UK, or Swiss Unipuller site is sold.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Payout Currency</strong></p>\r\n<p>Your \"Payout Currency\" is the currency used to settle the proceeds of your transactions into your Linked Financial Account. Typically, we determine your Payout Currency as outlined below, unless mutually agreed upon otherwise:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If you are a seller residing or established in the United States, your Payout Currency is the US Dollar.</li>\r\n<li>If you are a seller residing or established in an EEA country (except Iceland), your Payout Currency will be the Euro.</li>\r\n<li>If you are a seller residing or established in the United Kingdom, Switzerland, Liechtenstein, or Australia, your Payout Currency will be based on your country of residence.</li>\r\n<li>If you are a seller residing or established in Canada, your Payout Currency will be the Canadian Dollar or, if offered by us and selected by you, the US Dollar.</li>\r\n<li>If you are a seller residing or established in an Additional Country, then your Payout Currency is the US Dollar, or such other currency as we may offer and you may select, as determined by your country of residence.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>We reserve the right to introduce additional Payout Currencies at our discretion in the future. If your buyer pays for an item in a currency other than your Payout Currency, the paid amount will be converted into your Payout Currency before funds are disbursed to you. This conversion will use the applicable transaction exchange rate and include the currency conversion charge specified on our Fee Page in Section 3 (\"Seller Payment Fees\") below, provided it is agreed upon by you and your buyer.</p>\r\n<p>Additionally, if you reside in an Additional Country, the financial institution associated with your Linked Financial Account may charge a separate fee for converting your funds from the US Dollar to your local currency.</p>\r\n<p><strong>4. Seller Onboarding</strong></p>\r\n<p>To utilize our services, you must register and accept these Payments Terms of Use. If you reside in the EEA, the United Kingdom, or Switzerland, the submission of your Managed Payments online registration application constitutes your offer to enter into this agreement. If your onboarding is not immediately confirmed, you will receive notification of approval to receive services once we have reviewed your information.</p>\r\n<p>To use Managed Payments, you must:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Link a Financial Account:</strong> You need to link a financial account to receive settlements of proceeds from Managed Payments to this account, referred to as the \"Linked Financial Account.\" Depending on your location, specific requirements apply to the type of account, such as a bank account or a permitted alternative (e.g., debit card).</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Payout Currency:</strong> The currency used for settling your transaction proceeds to your Linked Financial Account is your \"Payout Currency.\" The determination of your Payout Currency is generally based on your country of residence, and specific criteria apply.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Verification Process:</strong> Completion of the Linked Financial Account verification process is necessary for payouts. Our assessment for security, risk purposes, and compliance with legal obligations typically takes up to two (2) days. If issues arise, the assessment is completed without undue delay.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Additional Countries:</strong> If you reside in an Additional Country, specific requirements may apply, including creating a Linked Financial Account with a designated non-bank third-party financial institution.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>By adding a Linked Financial Account to your Unipuller account, you confirm that you are the lawful owner of, or have the legal right to use, the Linked Financial Account. In certain circumstances, payouts may be directed to a Linked Financial Account owned or controlled by your legal representative, provided they have the authority to receive payouts on your behalf.</p>\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Information Submission:</strong> You must provide all necessary information for identity verification, compliance with laws and regulations, fraud prevention, and risk assessment. The required information may include personal details, business information (for business accounts), and government-issued identification.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Authentication:</strong> Provide information necessary for authentication, such as phone number or email validation. Failure to provide this information may hinder certain transactions or requests.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Information Accuracy:</strong> Maintain accurate information on file and consent to periodic updates based on information provided by you, your bank, or other payment services providers.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Compliance:</strong> Adhere to all applicable laws, regulations, rules, and terms and conditions related to your use of Unipuller Services. Payment Services should not be used for funds associated with gambling. Third-party terms and conditions for payment or settlement methods must be followed, and failure to comply may result in fees or actions by third parties.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Information Verification:</strong> Authorize Unipuller and its Affiliates to verify information provided by checking the existence of your bank account and obtaining reports from third-party sources, including banks, credit agencies, and data brokers. Failure to obtain or verify necessary information may result in account closure, suspension, or limitations on your access to services.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>It is crucial to provide accurate and complete information to avoid potential losses and ensure compliance with regulatory requirements.</p>\r\n<p><strong>4. Seller Onboarding</strong></p>\r\n<p>To utilize our services, you need to register and accept these Payments Terms of Use. If you are in the EEA, the United Kingdom, or Switzerland, your submission of the Managed Payments online registration application with Unipuller constitutes your offer to enter into this agreement. If your onboarding is not immediately confirmed, you will be notified of your approval to receive services after we review your information.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Using Managed Payments:</strong></p>\r\n<p>To engage with Managed Payments, you are required to:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Link a Financial Account:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If you reside in the United States, Canada, the United Kingdom, or Australia, your Linked Financial Account must be a bank account based in your country of residence or another accepted type (e.g., debit card).</li>\r\n<li>For those in the EEA (except Iceland), you may use a bank account located in any EEA member state (except Iceland) as your Linked Financial Account.</li>\r\n<li>Residents of Switzerland or Liechtenstein must provide a bank account located in Switzerland or Liechtenstein as their Linked Financial Account.</li>\r\n<li>If you reside in an Additional Country, you may need to create a Linked Financial Account with a specific non-bank third-party financial institution. There\'s also the option to use a bank account located in the Additional Country.</li>\r\n<li>If direct debits from your Linked Financial Account for Owed Amounts (as defined in Section 9) are not possible, you must maintain an alternative payment method on file. We reserve the right to withhold payouts until an alternative payment method is provided.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Currently, our Payment Services only facilitate disbursements to a Linked Financial Account. You can modify your Linked Financial Account at any time as allowed by us. Payouts are contingent upon (i) the completion of the Linked Financial Account verification process and (ii) our assessment for security, risk, and compliance with anti-money laundering and legal obligations. The assessment generally takes up to two (2) days following your completion of the verification process, or longer if any issues arise. If residing in an Additional Country and we offer the option to receive payouts to multiple Linked Financial Accounts, payouts will be distributed as per your instructions. By adding a Linked Financial Account to your Unipuller account, you affirm that you are the rightful owner of, or possess the legal right to use, any Linked Financial Account associated with your account. In specific situations, we may allow payouts to a Linked Financial Account owned or controlled by your legal representative, provided they have the authority, releasing us from liability for losses incurred from disbursements made to the legal representative under these Payments Terms of Use.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Provide Necessary Information:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Furnish all information required for purposes such as identity verification, compliance with laws and regulations (including anti-money laundering and sanctions screening obligations), managing settlements of your transaction proceeds, and assessing fraud and risk.</li>\r\n<li>For individuals, this information may include your full name, address, phone number, date of birth, taxpayer identification number, bank account information, and government-issued identification.</li>\r\n<li>For businesses, the information may include your full business name, address, phone number, entity type, bank account information, tax identification number, business number, and details about beneficial owners, directors, officers, authorized representatives, legal representatives, and primary contacts.</li>\r\n<li>Acknowledge that accurate contact information and other requested data are necessary for settling proceeds or issuing tax documents (e.g., United States Internal Revenue Service Form 1099K).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Authentication:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Provide information for the authentication of yourself or your payment transactions, including the validation of your phone number or email. Failure to provide this information may result in limitations on certain transactions or requests.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Maintain Information Accuracy:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Timely update and ensure the accuracy of information on file. Consent to periodic updates based on information provided by you, your bank, or other payment services providers. Only provide information about payment or settlement methods that you are authorized to use.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Compliance:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Adhere to all applicable laws, regulations, rules, and terms and conditions regarding your use of Unipuller Services. Payment Services should not be used for funds associated with gambling.</li>\r\n<li>Acknowledge that third parties (e.g., banks, credit and debit card issuers, networks, and payment services providers) may have their own terms and conditions for the payment or settlement methods chosen, and failure to comply may result in fees, delays, or other actions by such third parties.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>4. Seller Onboarding:</strong></p>\r\n<p>To access our services, complete registration, and agree to these Payments Terms of Use. If you are in the EEA, the United Kingdom, or Switzerland, your submission of the Managed Payments online registration application with Unipuller is considered your offer to enter this agreement. If your onboarding is not immediately confirmed, you\'ll be notified of approval after a review of your information.</p>\r\n<p>To utilize Managed Payments, follow these steps:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Connect a Financial Account:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Link a financial account to receive settlements from Managed Payments (referred to as \"Linked Financial Account\").</li>\r\n<li>If in the United States, Canada, the United Kingdom, or Australia, your Linked Financial Account must be a bank account in your country or another approved type (e.g., debit card).</li>\r\n<li>For residents of the EEA (except Iceland), a bank account in any EEA member state (except Iceland) is acceptable.</li>\r\n<li>Residents of Switzerland or Liechtenstein must provide a bank account in Switzerland or Liechtenstein.</li>\r\n<li>In an Additional Country, you may be required to create a Linked Financial Account with a specific non-bank third-party financial institution.</li>\r\n<li>If direct debits are not possible, you must keep another payment method on file, and payouts may be withheld until an alternative is provided.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Currently, Payment Services only facilitate disbursements to a Linked Financial Account. You can change it at any time as permitted. Payouts are subject to (i) completion of the Linked Financial Account verification process and (ii) our assessment for security, risk, and compliance with anti-money laundering and legal obligations. The assessment typically takes up to two (2) days after your verification process completion. For residents of Additional Countries, if offered multiple Linked Financial Accounts for payouts, allocations will follow your instructions. By adding a Linked Financial Account, you affirm lawful ownership or authorized usage. In certain cases, payouts to a Legal Representative\'s Linked Financial Account may be allowed, releasing us from liability for such disbursements.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Provide Necessary Information:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Furnish all information for identity verification, compliance with laws and regulations, management of settlement of transaction proceeds, and assessment of fraud and risk.</li>\r\n<li>For individuals, this includes full name, address, phone number, date of birth, taxpayer identification number, bank account info, and government-issued identification.</li>\r\n<li>For businesses, details include full business name, address, phone number, entity type, bank account information, tax identification number, business number, and beneficial owner(s), director(s), officer(s), authorized representative, legal representative, and/or primary contact information.</li>\r\n<li>Accurate contact information and other requested data are crucial for settling proceeds or issuing tax documents.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Authentication:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Provide information necessary for authentication, including phone number or email validation. Certain transactions or requests may be hindered without this information.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Maintain Information Accuracy:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Timely update and ensure information accuracy. Consent to periodic updates based on information from you, your bank, or other payment services providers. Only provide information about authorized payment or settlement methods.</li>\r\n<li>If information like country of residency is updated, repeat onboarding steps for continued use of Payment Services.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Compliance:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Adhere to all applicable laws, regulations, rules, and terms and conditions related to Unipuller Services use. Avoid using Payment Services for funds associated with gambling.</li>\r\n<li>Recognize that third parties may have their terms and conditions for payment or settlement methods, and failure to comply may result in fees, delays, or actions by such third parties.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>5. Shipping:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Upon notification of a buyer\'s payment through Managed Payments with Unipuller, promptly ship or deliver the item using the agreed-upon shipping method.</p>\r\n<p><strong>6. Managed Payments Limitations:</strong></p>\r\n<p>In specific listings or categories, sellers may offer buyers the option to pay directly for a purchase without using Unipuller\'s payment services (Offline Payment Methods). These methods, such as cash on pickup, are not covered by Unipuller\'s buyer protection programs. Unipuller does not handle payments for Offline Payment Methods and will not assist with payment disputes related to such methods, including chargebacks. Listings are subject to Unipuller\'s payment policies and additional terms on Unipuller Services regarding payments, including available payment and disbursement methods for these listings.</p>\r\n<p><strong>7. Using Managed Payments:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Returns and Cancellations; Refunds:</strong> If a buyer is eligible for a refund in a Managed Payments transaction due to a return or cancellation, in accordance with your agreement with the buyer or Unipuller\'s policies, you authorize Unipuller to make the corresponding refund payment to the buyer on your behalf.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Unipuller Buyer Protection Programs:</strong> Unipuller provides buyer protection programs, such as the \"Unipuller Money Back Guarantee\" (\"UMBG\"), on certain Unipuller Services to ensure buyers receive the ordered item or a refund. If a buyer successfully files a claim under such a program for a Managed Payments transaction, the Unipuller company offering the UMBG Service will reimburse the buyer on your behalf, following the applicable User Agreement and UMBG policy. You are obligated to reimburse the UMBG Service Provider for any such amounts, as per the User Agreement and UMBG policy.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Disputes:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A buyer may initiate a Dispute (chargeback, direct debit reversal, PayPal buyer protection claim, or payment dispute with their financial institution) in a Managed Payments transaction.</li>\r\n<li>Dispute resolution is determined by the buyer\'s financial institution.</li>\r\n<li>Unipuller will notify you when a Dispute is initiated and ask whether you accept or challenge it.</li>\r\n<li>If you accept, you agree to the payment reversal to the buyer.</li>\r\n<li>If you challenge, Unipuller will present your relevant evidence to the financial institution.</li>\r\n<li>Failure to provide requested information timely may impact the Dispute investigation outcome.</li>\r\n<li>If the buyer\'s financial institution decides in favor of the buyer, you are obligated to reimburse Unipuller for refunded amounts, unless you qualify for seller protection.</li>\r\n<li>Unipuller may choose to challenge the Dispute at its discretion, even if you accept it.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Optional Arbitration:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Some payment institutions offer an optional arbitration process to contest Dispute results.</li>\r\n<li>Unipuller may seek your consent to participate, and if agreed, Unipuller will represent and defend you.</li>\r\n<li>You are responsible for costs, including legal fees and arbitration fees.</li>\r\n<li>Unipuller is authorized to pay these amounts on your behalf during arbitration.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Seller Protection:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If you meet eligibility requirements and fulfill obligations under Unipuller\'s Seller Protection policy, you won\'t be held responsible for refunded amounts under the Unipuller Buyer Protection Program, Disputes, or unauthorized transactions using Unipuller spendable funds.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Fines, Penalties, and Losses:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Indemnify and reimburse Unipuller for losses arising from your breach of Payments Terms, User Agreement, violation of Unipuller\'s policies, violation of laws, or disputes related to items or services listed on Unipuller.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Holds:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unipuller reserves the right to manage risks by placing restrictions on your access to funds when necessary.</li>\r\n<li>Holds may be placed on funds for various reasons, and you\'ll be notified through the Unipuller Message Center and/or email.</li>\r\n<li>Relevant factors considered include selling history, seller performance, returns and cancellations, chargebacks, riskiness of the listing category, transaction value, ability to make direct debits, and Unipuller Buyer Protection Program claims.</li>\r\n<li>Holds may be canceled or proceed depending on the resolution of the issue.</li>\r\n<li>Unused retained amounts may be settled to your Linked Financial Account within 180 days of Unipuller account closure, unless otherwise required by law.</li>\r\n<li>Delays may occur due to your bank\'s holds and settlement procedures, beyond Unipuller\'s control.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reserves:</strong></p>\r\n<p>To manage risk or secure obligations under the Payments Terms of Use, Unipuller may require a reserve of transaction proceeds, which is a portion of your funds reserved as unavailable for disbursement. Reserves can take the form of rolling and/or minimum reserves.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Rolling Reserve:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A set percentage of transaction proceeds is withheld each day for a fixed period.</li>\r\n<li>Released to you on a rolling basis, e.g., a 10% rolling reserve for 60 days.</li>\r\n<li>Funds earned on day 1 withheld and released on day 61, and so forth.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Minimum Reserve:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hold a specific amount in your reserve.</li>\r\n<li>Funded by contributing a percentage of daily transaction proceeds or setting off the entire amount from pending payouts.</li>\r\n<li>For example, if a &pound;5,000 minimum reserve is required, it can be funded daily until reaching the amount or set off from pending payouts.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Reserves may be required based on risk factors, such as Unipuller account history, chargeback likelihood, customer claims, credit history, preselling orders, and extended delivery time frames.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Our Liability:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Unipuller is not liable for unauthorized, incorrect, unexecuted, or delayed payment transactions if reasonable precautions are taken and legal obligations are followed. This exclusion applies to issues beyond Unipuller\'s control due to abnormal and unforeseeable circumstances.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Signature:</strong></p>\r\n<p>In situations requiring your signature for anti-money laundering or legal requirements, Unipuller may consider your acceptance of Payments Terms of Use as equivalent, where not prohibited by applicable law.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Security; Third-Party Providers; Data Protection:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Security:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Acknowledge and adhere to security measures implemented by Unipuller for Managed Payments.</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for maintaining the security of login credentials.</li>\r\n<li>Responsible for transactions made using your Unipuller account.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Third-Party Providers:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unipuller may engage Affiliates or third-party providers for Managed Payments.</li>\r\n<li>Data transfer to such entities may occur for outsourced services.</li>\r\n<li>Acknowledgement that secrecy obligations do not apply to data transfer to such entities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Data Protection:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Acknowledge the processing of buyer\'s personal data during a sale.</li>\r\n<li>You, Responsible Payment Entity, and Payout Entity act as separate data controllers.</li>\r\n<li>Agree to comply with obligations as a data controller and provide reasonable cooperation for Unipuller\'s data controller obligations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Collection of Fees and Other Amounts You Owe:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Authorize Unipuller to collect owed amounts, including fees, fines, penalties, and taxes. Owed amounts may be collected through various methods, and you grant Unipuller the authority to choose the collection method.</p>\r\n<p>Methods include deducting from disbursements, recovering from Linked Financial Account or other payment instruments, or retaining collections agencies. Unipuller may charge you for unsuccessful attempts to recoup owed amounts.</p>\r\n<p>If SEPA/BACS direct debit mandate is provided, three days\' notice will be given before charging your bank account. Waiver of rights to receive advance notice of specific pre-authorized charges, unless you are an EU or UK consumer.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>10. Amendment:</strong></p>\r\n<p><em>All sellers (except consumers in Germany)</em></p>\r\n<p>Unipuller reserves the right to modify the Payments Terms of Use, notifying you in writing, e.g., through the website, Seller Hub, or Unipuller Message Center. Notification is at least 14 days before the expected effective date or:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Two (2) months prior if your Payout Entity is eBay Sarl or ECUK.</li>\r\n<li>Thirty (30) days prior if your Payout Entity is ECA.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Non-business consumers using eBay Sarl or ECUK as Payout Entity are considered to have consented unless explicitly rejected before the expected effective date. For other sellers, continued use implies acceptance.</p>\r\n<p><em>Consumers in Germany</em></p>\r\n<p>Notification at least two (2) months before expected effective date. Changes become effective based on your response:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>For material changes, active consent is required.</li>\r\n<li>For non-material changes, considered to have consented unless explicitly rejected before the expected effective date.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>A \"material change\" significantly shifts the balance to your disadvantage or establishes a new contract in Unipuller\'s favor. Changes due to legal requirements, court decisions, or injunctions are not considered material.</p>\r\n<p><em>Termination right in case of amendments (all sellers)</em></p>\r\n<p>Disagreeing with proposed changes allows termination without extra cost before the effective date. Amended terms are published on Unipuller\'s website.</p>\r\n<p><strong>11. Term, Termination:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unipuller may terminate with written notice, 14 days prior or two (2) months prior if eBay Sarl or ECUK is your Payout Entity.</li>\r\n<li>Termination may be immediate if required by law, for anti-money laundering, illegal activity suspicion, identity verification issues, or material contractual breaches.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Termination rights for sellers with eBay Sarl or ECUK as Payout Entity differ from those without. Post-termination, using Managed Payments implies acceptance.</p>\r\n<p>Termination does not affect accrued rights or liabilities, and surviving terms apply. Pending transactions at termination processed according to Payments Terms of Use unless prohibited by law. After termination, selling items on Unipuller Services is not possible.</p>\r\n<p><strong>12. Assignment:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Unipuller reserves the right to assign rights and obligations under Payments Terms of Use at its discretion. Sellers will be duly notified.</p>\r\n<p><strong>II. ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR SERVICES PROVIDED BY eCI:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Specific provisions for Payment Services provided by eCI.</li>\r\n<li>In case of conflict between User Agreement and Payments Terms of Use, the latter governs.</li>\r\n<li>eCI retains the right to change, discontinue, enhance, or modify features of Managed Payments at any time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>III. ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR SERVICES PROVIDED BY Unipuller:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Additional provisions for Payment Services from Unipuller.</li>\r\n<li>Payments Terms of Use govern in case of conflict with the User Agreement.</li>\r\n<li>Retains the right to change, discontinue, enhance, or modify features of Managed Payments at any time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>IV. ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR SERVICES PROVIDED BY ECCA:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Additional provisions for Payment Services from ECCA.</li>\r\n<li>Payments Terms of Use govern in case of conflict with the User Agreement.</li>\r\n<li>Retains the right to change, discontinue, enhance, or modify features of Managed Payments at any time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>V. ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR SERVICES PROVIDED BY ECA:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Additional provisions for Payment Services from ECA.</li>\r\n<li>Payments Terms of Use govern in case of conflict with the User Agreement.</li>\r\n<li>Retains the right to change, discontinue, enhance, or modify features of Managed Payments at any time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>VI. ADDITIONAL TERMS FOR SERVICES PROVIDED BY ECUK:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Additional provisions for Payment Services from ECUK.</li>\r\n<li>Payments Terms of Use govern in case of conflict with the User Agreement.</li>\r\n<li>Retains the right to change, discontinue, enhance, or modify features of Managed Payments at any time. Notification of material changes or modifications provided through Unipuller messages or directly to the linked email address.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>2. Execution of Payment Transactions:</strong></p>\r\n<p>When utilizing Managed Payments as a payee or payer, payment transactions will adhere to the rules and procedures of the payment schemes or as mutually agreed upon.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Required Information:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Your payer (e.g., the buyer of your Unipuller item) must ensure the necessary data is provided for payment transaction execution. If we lack sufficient data, we reserve the right to request it from your payer\'s payment service provider.</p>\r\n<p>The required information includes:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Your name</li>\r\n<li>Your Unipuller username</li>\r\n<li>Buyer\'s name (if applicable)</li>\r\n<li>Buyer\'s Unipuller username and any other data required by the buyer\'s payment service provider or us (if applicable)</li>\r\n<li>Currency of the payment transaction (preferably in abbreviated form)</li>\r\n<li>Amount of the payment transaction</li>\r\n<li>Beneficiary\'s payment details</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Additional information, like a one-time authorization code sent to your verified phone number or email address, may be necessary for authentication. We will use information stored in our systems to the extent reasonably possible. Incomplete or inaccurate information may result in nonexecution or defective execution of the payment transaction, and we disclaim liability for associated damages or delays.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Receipt of Payment Orders:</strong></p>\r\n<p>A payment order is considered received:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Executed via a payment card, following the card scheme\'s rules</li>\r\n<li>Received through available electronic communication channels, on the business day when actually received by us</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If not received on a business day, it\'s deemed received on the next business day. \"Business days\" refer to days when banks in London are open for regular business. Once received, a payment order cannot be revoked, except with a pre-agreed future execution date, revocable until the business day before the agreed date.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Refusal of Payment Orders:</strong></p>\r\n<p>We reserve the right to refuse the execution of a payment order under the following circumstances:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Factual errors or incompleteness in the payment order information</li>\r\n<li>Nonfulfillment of obligations under these Payments Terms of Use or any other agreement</li>\r\n<li>Doubts about the validity of the instruction or the identity/authority of the person providing the payment order</li>\r\n<li>Execution would breach applicable rules, laws, or regulations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Reasonable fees may apply for such refusals. You acknowledge that, during execution, we may disclose information, including your legal address, to the payer\'s payment service provider and, if applicable, intermediaries involved in the transaction. As the payer, transaction execution may depend on us receiving the respective amount from you before execution.</p>\r\n<p><strong>3. Settlement of Funds:</strong></p>\r\n<p>If Unipuller is designated as your Payout Entity, the initiation of proceeds settlement to your Linked Financial Account will occur. Payments are typically initiated based on your preselected schedule or \"on demand\" following individual payment instructions from you. In cases where your payment account lacks a regular settlement schedule, available funds may be periodically swept and sent to your Linked Financial Account.</p>\r\n<p>Transaction proceeds, excluding those held according to these Payments Terms of Use, are consolidated into a batch for settlement based on the agreed payout schedule. For instance, if you opt for weekly payouts, a single settlement is automatically initiated once a week for all transactions ready for disbursement on that day. Alternatively, if you request a payout on demand, a single settlement is initiated for all eligible transactions on that day. You may choose to have only a portion of your available transaction proceeds paid out, leaving the remainder in your payment account. Transaction proceeds are expected to be available for disbursement approximately one to two business days after the buyer completes the order. However, actual availability may vary based on the buyer\'s payment method and when the payment transaction is received by us. We may deviate from the settlement process as necessary for compliance or risk reasons. The balance in your payment account is not considered a deposit, and no interest or earnings will be provided on the funds held.</p>\r\n<p>If Unipuller is unable to settle your proceeds, the resolution may involve refunding the buyer (e.g., due to technical processing issues) or processing the funds according to applicable law. Monthly statements of your transactions will be provided free of charge and can be accessed in the Seller Hub.</p>\r\n<p><strong>4. Liability for Unauthorized Payment Transactions:</strong></p>\r\n<p>You bear full liability for losses related to an unauthorized payment transaction if you engage in fraudulent conduct regarding the transaction or fail to fulfill obligations under this agreement, such as keeping your credentials secure or promptly notifying us, with intent or gross negligence.</p>\r\n<p><strong>5. Our Liability:</strong></p>\r\n<p>We commit to refunding you in full and assume liability for losses directly and reasonably foreseeable in case of an incorrectly or nonexecuted payment transaction. This commitment is contingent on you informing us of such a transaction defect without undue delay, no later than thirteen (13) months after the transaction\'s execution, unless we failed to provide information about the transaction within that timeframe.</p>\r\n<p>To the maximum extent allowed by applicable law, neither we nor our Affiliates (including employees, directors, agents, and representatives) shall be liable for direct or indirect lost profits or any special, incidental, or consequential damages arising from or related to these Payments Terms of Use or Managed Payments. Furthermore, our aggregate liability and that of our Affiliates shall not exceed the actual amount of direct damages (excluding direct loss of profits) under these Payments Terms of Use, irrespective of the legal basis.</p>\r\n<p>We and our Affiliates shall not be liable for any failure or delay in performing obligations under these Payments Terms of Use if caused by unforeseeable circumstances beyond our control or where bound by other legal obligations as covered by applicable law.</p>\r\n<p><strong>6. Shipping Labels:</strong></p>\r\n<p>If a buyer purchases a return shipping label at their expense on the Unipuller website, Unipuller may deduct the label costs from the refund amount received by the buyer. In this scenario, you agree (as a debtor to the buyer for the refund) to be assigned as a debtor to the shipping carrier for the label costs. You authorize us to use the relevant part of the refund amount to pay the shipping carrier on your behalf, and no additional shipping costs will be incurred.</p>\r\n<p><strong>7. Corrective Measures:</strong></p>\r\n<p>In the event of suspected or actual fraud or security threats affecting your Unipuller account, we will notify you by email and provide instructions on securing your account.</p>\r\n<p><strong>8. General Provisions:</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you are a business using these payment services in managed payments, specific articles of the Payment Services Regulations 2017 will not apply to your use.</p>\r\n<p>For individuals using the Payment Services, you may not utilize them to receive or transfer funds on behalf of another person or entity.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Complaints:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Any complaints about Unipuller or its services should be directed to Unipuller. Responses to such complaints from Unipuller may be sent to you via email. If dissatisfied with Unipuller\'s response, you have the option to escalate the complaint to the FCA or the Financial Ombudsman Services, depending on your location.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Communication:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Communication will be conducted in the languages in which these Payments Terms of Use were provided. Notices or information may be provided by posting in your Unipuller Account, emailing to your registered email address, mailing to your registered physical address, calling your phone number, or sending mobile messages.</p>\r\n<p>Legal notices to Unipuller should be mailed to the specified address. You can request copies of legally required disclosures, and they will be provided in a format allowing storage and reproduction.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Governing Law and Jurisdiction:</strong></p>\r\n<p>These Payments Terms of Use are governed by the laws of England and Wales. If acting as a consumer, judicial proceedings can be brought before the competent court of your residence or Unipuller\'s place of business. If acting as a business seller, you agree to the exclusive jurisdiction of the English courts.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 1, 5, 5, '2023-12-17 20:25:03', '2023-12-18 02:25:03');

